\details{
\strong{Ordered pipeline.} Four fixed steps run in order: coerce each column
to its CDISC dataType, reorder columns to the spec, sort rows by the
dataset keys, then stamp the metadata. A spec variable the data lacks is
never fabricated as an empty column: artoo is a lossless carrier, not a
deriver. It is reported instead, an informational heads-up at apply time
plus a \code{missing_variable} finding (when mandatory) or \code{missing_permissible}
(when not), and left absent, so the conformed frame carries only the
columns the data actually had.

\strong{Extras are kept by default.} A column the spec does not declare
survives the pipeline (ordered after the declared ones), is \emph{reported}
by the \code{extra_variable} conformance finding, and round-trips through
every \verb{write_*()} codec with metadata inferred from its R class —
membership reported, never enforced by silent destruction. Keeping is
the default because artoo is lossless by construction: a
metadata-application step that silently discarded columns would break
that contract, so trimming data is always an explicit, announced choice
rather than a default side effect.
\code{extra = "drop"} opts in to trim-to-spec (the returned frame carries
exactly the spec's columns): the undeclared columns are removed \emph{before}
the check, so the findings describe exactly the returned frame (a dropped
column is never reported as \code{extra_variable}), and the drop itself is
always announced (\code{artoo_message_apply}) as the audit trail of what was
removed — even under \code{conformance = "off"}.

\strong{Lossless or abort, your call.} A coercion that would damage values —
an \code{integer} dataType truncating fractions or overflowing R's 32-bit
range — aborts with \code{artoo_error_type} before any value is touched, under
the default \code{on_coercion_loss = "error"}. This gate is independent of
\code{conformance}: \code{conformance = "off"} does not bypass it. When the data
(not the spec) is right, set \code{on_coercion_loss = "keep"}: the column
keeps its wider source type and the divergence is reported as an
\code{integer_fraction} / \code{integer_overflow} finding, never silently
truncated. When the spec is wrong, retype it with \code{\link[=set_type]{set_type()}} (or
\code{\link[=repair_spec]{repair_spec()}} from the findings). The error abort carries the offending
rows as data: \code{cnd$variables} is a data frame with columns
\code{variable}, \code{data_type}, \code{n}, and \code{reason} (\code{"truncated"} /
\code{"overflowed"}), so a pipeline can collect every mismatch in one
\code{tryCatch(..., artoo_error_type = function(cnd) cnd$variables)} pass.
